Prose-feasibility audit. At each passage below, some world-states are
ambiguous when the player arrives — some players hold them, some don't, and
the prose must read true for both. A STATE is one dilemma's open question;
its flags below are sides and facets of that ONE uncertainty — they count
together, as one state. A writer can honor at most {{ cap }} such states in
one passage.

For each passage, two honest tools:
1. "irrelevant": flags the prose should NOT address — states that may hold
   but don't touch this scene ("don't mention the romance in the vault
   heist"). Marking a state irrelevant means listing ALL of its flags.
   What you leave relevant, the writer must honor.
2. "split_on": dilemmas this scene genuinely turns on, when too many
   matter to fit the cap. The engine re-presents the passage as gated
   variant pages — each variant's readers arrive holding a KNOWN side, so
   that state stops counting and each variant's prose commits to its side.
   Split on at most 2 dilemmas per passage. **An [ENDING] passage cannot
   split** — variants would multiply the story's ending set, fixed at the
   freeze — so resolve an over-cap ending ONLY by marking the state(s) it
   does not address as irrelevant; leave its split_on empty.

The audit is about honesty, not budget: never mark a state irrelevant just
to hit the number — if the scene turns on it, split on it instead. Where a
passage is over the cap, you MUST resolve the excess (irrelevant where
honest, split_on where not): states − splits ≤ {{ cap }}.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}.

PASSAGES:
{% for p in passages %}
- {{ p.passage.id }}{% if p.passage.ending %} [ENDING — resolve over-cap by irrelevant only, never split]{% endif %}: {{ p.passage.summary }}
  ambiguous states: {{ p.states | length }}{% if p.over %} — {{ p.over }} over the cap: resolve at least {{ p.over }} ({% if p.passage.ending %}irrelevant only{% else %}irrelevant or split_on{% endif %}){% endif %}

{% for s in p.states %}
  - state {{ s.dilemma }} ("{{ s.question }}"), its flags:
{% for flag, text in s.flags %}
    - {{ flag }}: {{ text }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- One entry per passage above: {"passage": id, "irrelevant": [flag ids],
  "split_on": [dilemma ids] or omit}. An empty irrelevant list means every
  state matters in that scene.
- A state that the passage's own beats grant or directly pay off is never
  irrelevant there.
